<dl id="n38219a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38219a">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38219a"> 219(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> dharma</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">To clinch the matter, the keeping of caste became for Hindus their &ldquo;practical&rdquo; religion (<i><mark>dharma</mark></i>), and contravention of it the sin entailing the heaviest retribution. <small> Rev W.S. Hunt, <a name="WSHI" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WSHI"><cite title="source">India's Outcastes: A New Era</cite></a> (1924) 22-23</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Dharma: In India, social or caste custom; right behaviour; law; esp. in Buddhism and Hinduism: moral law, truth (OED).  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c08043c" href="c8all.htm#c08043c">VI.C.08:043(c)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
